</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="820B36BEFFD5FFBEFF7BFABEFA8EFA25" blockId="105.[189,1399,1377,1438]" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">
Submontane to low subalpine, 385–1700 (2000?) m a.s.l.; submontane-montane mixed and coniferous forests; under 
<taxonomicName id="45B44D3DFFD5FFBEFEA3FA59FE03FA25" box="[357,430,1413,1438]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fagaceae" genus="Fagus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B0C0EAACFFD5FFBEFEA3FA59FE03FA25" box="[357,430,1413,1438]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Fagus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="45B44D3DFFD5FFBEFE21FA58FDB3FA25" box="[487,542,1412,1438]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Sapindaceae" genus="Acer" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="105" pageNumber="106" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B0C0EAACFFD5FFBEFE21FA58FDB3FA25" box="[487,542,1412,1438]" italics="true" pageId="105" pageNumber="106">Acer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
leaf litter, also under moss and bark on tree trunk, once in a cave.
</paragraph>
